To solve this problem, we can move the SpawnBalloon() method call inside the Update() method, which is called once per frame. This way, the method will only be called once and with the correct arguments.

In addition, we added some error checking and input validation to the SpawnBalloon() method.

Finally, we moved the setting of the nextSpawnTime variable outside of the if statement, so that it is always set to the correct value, regardless of whether the balloon is spawned or not.
